Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the tip of the @broccoli{1}.
Cut head into small florets and stem into 2cm chunks.

Pop the broccoli onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the edges are crispy and slightly
charred, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, boil a large #pot of salted @water{to taste} for the salmon.

Place a pan over medium heat (without oil).

Once the pan is hot, add the @pine nuts{10%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until
lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once toasted, remove from the pan and set aside. Reserve the pan for later use!

> Keep an eye on the pine nuts so they don't burn!

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved and sliced).

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(grated) (or use a garlic press).

Zest and quarter the @lemon{1}(quartered).

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}(chopped) (stalks and all).

Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{2%pack} in a #sieve.

Meanwhile, return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle @oil{to taste} and a
knob of @butter{to taste}.

Fry the garlic and half the onion until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @mustard{1%sachet}, beans, @Hello Muscat{1%sachet}, lemon zest and two-thirds
of the chopped parsley.

Warm through for ~{2-3%minutes} then remove from the heat. Mash the beans with a
#fork until you've got a smooth consistency.

Loosen with a splash of @?milk{to taste}, if desired. Season to taste with
@salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and lemon juice.

Once the water for the salmon has come to a boil, reduce the heat to medium-high.

Pop in the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet} and remaining onion.

Add the @salmon{200%g} to the #pot (skin-side down).

Leave to simmer until the fish is cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish. Salmon is cooked when opaque
> in the middle.

Once cooked, drain the salmon and onion.

Divide the cannellini bean mash between plates and top with the salmon and onions.

Serve the roasted broccoli, toasted pine nuts and lemon wedges alongside.

Garnish with a sprinkling of remaining chopped parsley.